Saruman, servant of the eye X4    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">What makes this deck good is strategh, especially on the free peoples side.  I can make gandalf have a vitallity of 6 and, with sam and arwen and &#39;trust me as u once did&#39; down i can make ANYONE stength plus 15!<br>
<br>
Another way to beef other guys is put the sword on merry.  After site 5 play &#39;depart silently&#39;, then exert my boromir to add even MORE strength to merry.  Then I can double-exert him to make someone, potentially, +47 strength!!!!!<br>
<br>
<br>
On that note, here&#39;s a question.....Merry has a vitallity of 4.....Let&#39;s simply say he&#39;s at normal strength (3).  Let&#39;s say gandalf is losing in a skirmish by 4.  Can I double-exert merry (he now has 2 vitallity left), use one strength of spirit from hand(he has 3 vitallity left), and then double-exert merry again?  That&#39;s a question that needs answering.......If I can do that then I cna make someone +131 (in theory, its A) never going to be needed and B) never going to happen BUT IT COULD!)<br>
<br>
On that note, Can I exert an exaughsted companion but then cancel the exertion?  The card says if they are ABOUT to exert......so technically it can happen........right?<br>
<br>
<br>
Ok, back to my strategy.  I use my allies to heal my guys, wound theres (during archery with rumil and during regroup with calaglin) oor lessen their strength.<br>
<br>
Idealy, I play the tale of gil-galad on rumil so i can dish-out 3 wounds during archery to the minions of my choice.......<br>
<br>
That&#39;s the essence of the free peoples strategy....<br>
<br>
Shadow strategy:<br>
<br>
It&#39;s the same thing as last time, but uruk-hai rampage, with the ability to make guys fierce, makes it better.......<br>
<br>
Needless to say, fellowship archer decks get DEMOLISHED by my anti-archery cards.  This isn&#39;t ideal, I&#39;m trying to get some more uruk fighters, uruk raiders and an uruk blood lust or 2 to take its place.......But as of now archery decks get hit pretty bad when its my shadow turn<br>
<br>
<br>
If u forget the rest of the strategy, check the shadow strat from &#39;low rare smack&#39;, its pretty much the same......<br>
<br>
<br>
alright, rate it and keep in mind that a strategy u dont understand isnt always a bad strategy.... </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
